South Africa has recorded 60% more excess deaths than expected in the last few weeks. eNCA speaks to Wits University vaccinology professor, Shabir Madhi. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Wits vaccinology professor Shabir Madhi says the under-reporting of COVID-19 deaths is systemic and not unique to South Africa. South Africa has recorded 60 percent more excess deaths than expected in the last few weeks. This is raising questions about whether or not the recorded number of COVID-19 deaths is accurate. READ: Mkhize concedes COVID-19 related deaths not reported timeously Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said there is nothing untoward about the surge in COVID-19 related deaths in the past few days. He said it indicates a backlog in reporting deaths timeously. Madhi says some people may die of COVID-19 outside of hospitals or before they get tested. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.